Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly increased liver enzymes (ALT, ALP), which may indicate hepatic or biliary involvement. Albumin is slightly above normal, but other parameters are within reference ranges. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and liver function.
